Boil a half-full #kettle{}.

While it boils, heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, fry the @Diced British Chicken Breast{260%g} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook, ~{5-6%minutes}. IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw meat.

Meanwhile, pour the boiled water into a #saucepan{} with @salt{1/4%tsp} on high heat.

Boil the @Jasmine Rice{150%g}, ~{10-12%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain and pop back in the pan. Cover.

In the meantime, quarter the @Lime{1}.

Add the @Tomato Puree{30%g} to the chicken. Cook, ~{30%seconds}.

Stir in the @Ginger Puree{15%g}, @Coconut Milk{200%ml}, @Soy Sauce{15%ml}, @Chicken Stock Paste{10%g} and @Sugar{1/2%tsp}. Simmer, ~{3-4%minutes}. IMPORTANT: Cook the chicken so there's no pink in the middle.

Add the @Baby Spinach{40%g} in handfuls, making sure it's piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Add a good squeeze of lime juice. Remove from the heat.

Share the rice between your #bowls{}.

Top with the chicken stew.

Serve with any remaining lime quarters.

Enjoy!